Each time the developer wants to check if his source code is trustworthy and if the trustworthy features are&#xD;
well-implemented, he shall be able to make the checks and to decide the modifications he has to take into account.&lt;/span></mainDescription>
  <keyConsiderations>These checks make sense in Java but not in Opa where the Trustworthiness is natively taken into account.</keyConsiderations>
  <sections xmi:id="_XKZ7wPlyEeST16WGbo409w" name="Check the component  " guid="_XKZ7wPlyEeST16WGbo409w">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;span lang=&quot;IT&quot; style='FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: &quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;; mso-fareast-font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-ansi-language: IT; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA'>&#xD;
For the whole source code, check if the trustworthiness profile given in input is reached for the current&#xD;
development.&lt;/span></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_Y25SwPlyEeST16WGbo409w" name="Analyse the check results" guid="_Y25SwPlyEeST16WGbo409w">
